living-concrete.knowledge:
LLMs default to verbose Dart naming. We compress by scope:
private: _procExec, _fsOp, tmpBuf (aggressive abbreviation)
public: AppCtx, ConfigMgr, ProcCtrlBlk (conservative — safe abbrevs)
local: fd, pid, buf, ctx (scope determines brevity)
test: eng, asm, ctx, streamFut (max density)

living-concrete.pattern:
if (!cond) return fail; // guard — happy path at top level
NOT: if (cond) { 15 lines; return ok; } return fail;
Early return over nested if-else. Switch expression over if-else chain.

Catch when recovery/business logic exists:
  try { validate(); } catch (PermEx e) { return unauth(); }
  try { return fast(); } catch (CacheEx) { return slow(); }
Let infrastructure exceptions bubble. Never catch-and-rethrow.

// SETUP: eng = Engine(asm); eng.init();
// BEHAVIOR: eng.add(Event.text('x')); await Future.delayed(Duration.zero);
// VERIFY: expect(eng.state, isA<X>(), reason: 'why');
reason: param replaces comments. Manual mocks, no mockito.
